    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive setup, anchored by a trio of elite plays. **Tyler Soderstrom** leads the charge with a 76.91 score, capitalizing on a favorable matchup against Leiter and a high-reward park factor that elevates his power ceiling. Hot on his heels are **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). **Mickey Moniak** is particularly intriguing; despite the lineup being pending, his massive 14% platoon boost against the soft-tossing Ryan Weiss makes him a primary engine for our production today. We are also leaning into the speed-first profile of **Brice Turang** (64.27); facing a slow-moving southpaw, his aggressive 86% SB efficiency projection against the opposing battery is a calculated gamble to keep us competitive in the league\u2019s scarcest category.\n\nThe most notable bench decision involves the thin margins between our lower-tier starters and potential backups. **Kyle Karros** (50.77) narrowly cleared the \"marginal\" start threshold despite an assumed #8 spot in the order. He edged out the rest of the bench depth\u2014which remains dormant today due to off-days for **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story**\u2014primarily because of the favorable 7.36 xERA matchup against Ryan Weiss. While **Luis Campusano** (43.78) holds a tenuous spot, his low order placement remains a risk; if we see a confirmed lineup drop him further or if **Gabriel Moreno** or **Dalton Rushing** were available in a better spot, that floor could vanish. We are monitoring weather reports closely for the games featuring **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Jose Caballero**, as the wind out at their venue significantly boosts their respective scores, but both players remain locked in as strong starters who provide essential depth against the Suter-led staff.",
